00:33:55,601 --> 00:33:57,334
BUT YOU HAVE TO CHOOSE
THE RIGHT WAY--

429
00:33:57,334 --> 00:33:58,968
NEITHER TOO FINE
NOR TOO GRAINY.

430
00:33:58,968 --> 00:34:00,834
WHEN THE WATER
IS A LITTLE OVER 90°

431
00:34:00,834 --> 00:34:02,834
AND ALMOST BOILING,
IT IS FORCED THROUGH THE COFFEE

432
00:34:02,834 --> 00:34:04,634
AT A PRESSURE
OF NINE ATMOSPHERES.

433
00:34:04,634 --> 00:34:07,000
AND THIS SHOULD TAKE
EXACTLY 24 SECONDS.

434
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:09,367
IF IT TAKES MORE THAN 24 SECONDS,
THE COFFEE IS TOO FINE.

435
00:34:09,367 --> 00:34:12,000
IF IT TAKES LESS THAN 24 SECONDS,
THE COFFEE IS TOO GRAINY.

436
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:15,000
YOU CAN PRACTICE
USING THIS STOPWATCH.

437
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:17,133
BUT IN TIME YOU WILL COME
TO LEARN BY HEART

438
00:34:17,133 --> 00:34:20,300
THE DURATION
OF THE MAGIC 24 SECONDS.

439
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:47,200
WHY DON'T YOU EVEN TASTE THEM?

440
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:49,400
IT WOULD BE AN OFFENSE
TO MY TASTE BUDS.

441
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:51,601
YOU JUST DON'T EXPOSE THEM
TO SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

442
00:34:51,601 --> 00:34:53,367
WELL, I CAN'T SEE
WHAT'S WRONG WITH IT.

443
00:34:53,367 --> 00:34:56,767
- IT'S BLACK, IT'S HOT--
- IT'S DISGUSTING.

444
00:35:15,667 --> 00:35:19,033
THIS IS BUTRAGUEÑO...

445
00:35:19,033 --> 00:35:21,033
<i>...THE FAMOUS BULL.</i>

446
00:35:21,033 --> 00:35:25,033
<i>BUENOS DIAS,</i> BUTRAGUEÑO,
YOU CRAZY CATHOLIC FUCK.

447
00:35:26,367 --> 00:35:28,567
LUCKY BASTARD--

448
00:35:28,567 --> 00:35:30,801
FUCKING THOSE BEAUTIFUL
COWS ALL DAY LONG.

449
00:36:15,067 --> 00:36:18,067
WHY THE FUCK
DID YOU BUY A DUCK?

450
00:36:18,067 --> 00:36:19,767
<i>IT'S OUR CHRISTMAS</i>
<i>DINNER, LUCAS.</i>

451
00:36:19,767 --> 00:36:22,567
WE'RE GOING TO FEED IT
WITH ORANGES AND GINGER

452
00:36:22,567 --> 00:36:24,801
AND FRESH ESTRAGON
AND COGNAC.

453
00:36:24,801 --> 00:36:27,000
WE'RE GONNA MARINATE IT
FROM THE INSIDE OUT.

454
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:30,200
- WE CAN'T KILL A FELLOW DUCK.
- <i>YES, WE CAN, LUCAS.</i>

455
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:33,601
MY MOUTH'S WATERING
JUST THINKING ABOUT IT.

456
00:36:48,634 --> 00:36:52,467
<i>WHAT THE FUCK'S</i>
<i>GOING ON HERE?</i>

457
00:36:54,167 --> 00:36:58,567
OKAY, YOU LET ME KNOW
HOW THIS ONE IS.

458
00:37:01,501 --> 00:37:03,267
- HERE YOU ARE.
- THANK YOU.

459
00:37:13,067 --> 00:37:15,167
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

460
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:19,000
I THOUGHT IT WOULD
BE A SHAME

461
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,000
TO LET ALL THOSE
ESPRESSOS GO TO WASTE

462
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,734
WHILE I MASTER
THE TECHNIQUE,

463
00:37:22,734 --> 00:37:24,734
SO I THOUGHT
WE COULD TAKE IT

464
00:37:24,734 --> 00:37:26,667
AS AN OPPORTUNITY
TO HELP PEOPLE.

465
00:37:28,300 --> 00:37:32,601
- HELP PEOPLE?
- YES, HELP PEOPLE.

466
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,934
ARE YOU OUT
OF YOUR FUCKING MIND?

467
00:37:38,067 --> 00:37:41,267
WE'RE RUNNING A BUSINESS HERE,
NOT A GODDAMN SHELTER.

468
00:37:41,267 --> 00:37:43,901
<i>NOW GET THESE LOSERS</i>
<i>OUT OF MY SIGHT!</i>

469
00:37:43,901 --> 00:37:46,367
FINISH YOUR--
JACQUES...

470
00:37:46,367 --> 00:37:49,267
AREN'T YOU SOMETIMES AFRAID
THAT YOU'LL GO STRAIGHT TO HELL?

471
00:37:51,601 --> 00:37:54,334
CHRISTOPHER, YOU CAN FINISH
YOUR COFFEE. IT'S FINE.

472
00:37:54,334 --> 00:37:55,834
GO!

473
00:37:57,367 --> 00:37:59,767
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.
THANK YOU.

474
00:38:03,067 --> 00:38:05,267
WHAT ARE WE GONNA
CALL YOU?

475
00:38:09,801 --> 00:38:13,133
ESTRAGON?

476
00:38:13,133 --> 00:38:16,133
OKAY.

477
00:38:16,133 --> 00:38:18,067
ESTRAGON.

478
00:38:28,434 --> 00:38:31,133
BAR'S CLOSED.
GET THE FUCK OUT.

479
00:38:31,133 --> 00:38:34,367
WE UNDERSTAND THAT YOU'RE
THE OWNER OF THIS BUILDING.

480
00:38:34,367 --> 00:38:36,434
CORRECT.

481
00:38:36,434 --> 00:38:38,267
WE'RE BUYING BUILDINGS
IN THIS AREA

482
00:38:38,267 --> 00:38:41,100
AND WE'RE INTERESTED IN LOOKING
INTO BUYING THIS ONE TOO.

483
00:38:41,100 --> 00:38:47,100
WELL, FOR A BILLION DOLLARS

484
00:38:47,100 --> 00:38:50,767
I'LL GIVE YOU A SCENIC TOUR
OF MY ANAL CANAL.

485
00:38:50,767 --> 00:38:53,467
HOW DO YOU LIKE
THEM APPLES?

486
00:38:53,467 --> 00:38:55,634
IT WOULDN'T HURT
TO SIT DOWN FOR A WHILE--

487
00:38:55,634 --> 00:38:59,267
GODDAMN, YOU'RE LIKE A PIECE
OF SHIT THAT JUST WON'T FLUSH.

488
00:38:59,267 --> 00:39:02,534
NOW GET THE FUCK OUT OF
HERE BEFORE I GET RUDE.

489
00:39:06,167 --> 00:39:07,767
LET'S GO, GUYS.

490
00:39:11,834 --> 00:39:16,367
"A WALK IN THE MISTS
OF TIME AND SPACE."

491
00:39:16,367 --> 00:39:20,133
- WHAT IS THAT?
- IT'S THE TITLE OF MY BOOK.

492
00:39:20,133 --> 00:39:22,434
I LIKE IT.
I'M LOOKING FORWARD TO READING THAT.

493
00:39:22,434 --> 00:39:24,133
YEAH, WELL, I'M STUCK THOUGH.
I'M BLOCKED.

494
00:39:24,133 --> 00:39:26,267
COME ON, YOU GOT IT
IN YOUR BLOOD.

495
00:39:26,267 --> 00:39:28,300
YOU'RE JULES VERNE'S
GREAT-GREAT-GRANDSON.

496
00:39:28,300 --> 00:39:31,434
- YEAH, BUT THINK OF THE PRESSURE.
- FORGET ABOUT IT.

497
00:39:31,434 --> 00:39:34,267
YOU COULD DO IT.
YOU GOT IT IN YOUR BLOOD.

498
00:39:34,267 --> 00:39:37,834
- JUST WRITE IT.
- OKAY.

499
00:40:18,801 --> 00:40:21,667
- SHE GAVE ME HER NUMBER,
BUT AS SHE WAS WRITING IT OUT,

500
00:40:21,667 --> 00:40:23,868
SHE GOES, "DON'T CALL ME
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS."

501
00:40:23,868 --> 00:40:26,667
AND I SAID, "HOW COME?"
SHE SAID, "WELL, I'M GONNA--"

502
00:40:26,667 --> 00:40:29,267
AH, I CAN'T
TAKE THIS ANYMORE!

503
00:40:29,267 --> 00:40:30,834
WE ARE ALL ANIMALS.

504
00:40:30,834 --> 00:40:33,234
ESTRAGON, YOU MUST
BE LIBERATED.

505
00:40:33,234 --> 00:40:35,234
- <i>TAKE IT EASY.</i>
- <i>COME ON, DARLING.</i>

506
00:40:35,234 --> 00:40:36,934
OUT OUT.

507
00:40:36,934 --> 00:40:38,367
COME ON, OUT,
SWEETHEART.

508
00:40:42,501 --> 00:40:44,934
<i>ESTRAGON, MY FRIEND,</i>
<i>YOU MUST BE LIBERATED.</i>

509
00:40:47,734 --> 00:40:49,167
<i>I'M OFFERING YOU FREEDOM</i>

510
00:40:49,167 --> 00:40:52,267
<i>AND YOU GO BACK</i>
<i>INTO INCARCERATION.</i>

511
00:41:07,033 --> 00:41:08,968
PHIL.

512
00:41:12,701 --> 00:41:16,100
- THIS ONE, RIGHT?
- YEAH, MM-HMM.

513
00:41:16,100 --> 00:41:18,567
LISTEN, LUCAS, I DIDN'T
BRING TOO MUCH CASH WITH ME.

514
00:41:18,567 --> 00:41:20,400
CAN I BRING IT IN
TO YOU TOMORROW?

515
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:22,868
I HAVE A TIP
I CAN LEAVE YA.

516
00:41:22,868 --> 00:41:25,067
- YOU THINK IT'LL BE OKAY?
- YEAH, SURE.

517
00:41:25,067 --> 00:41:27,501
- THANKS.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

518
00:41:29,567 --> 00:41:33,300
HOW'S-- HOW'S
YOUR MOTHER DOING?

519
00:41:33,300 --> 00:41:34,734
SHE'S DYING.

520
00:41:34,734 --> 00:41:36,267
SHE MIGHT BE
ABLE TO COME HOME

521
00:41:36,267 --> 00:41:37,834
FROM THE HOSPITAL
A COUPLE DAYS A WEEK,

522
00:41:37,834 --> 00:41:39,434
BUT I DON'T KNOW
IF SHE'S GONNA MAKE IT.

523
00:41:39,434 --> 00:41:41,267
HERE'S TO MOOTY.

524
00:41:41,267 --> 00:41:43,534
- MOOTY.
- HERE'S TO MOOTY.

525
00:41:47,801 --> 00:41:52,067
MY BOY, YOU'RE MAKING
ONE VERY SERIOUS MISTAKE.

526
00:41:52,067 --> 00:41:53,968
- WHAT?
- YOU'RE BEING FRIENDLY.

527
00:41:53,968 --> 00:41:56,000
- WHAT'S WRONG WITH THAT?
- REMEMBER WHAT I SAY:

528
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:58,567
NEVER BE FRIENDLY
WITH A CUSTOMER.

529
00:41:58,567 --> 00:42:00,334
BE FAMILIAR,
BUT NOT FRIENDLY.

530
00:42:00,334 --> 00:42:03,000
FAMILIAR BUT NOT FRIENDLY.

531
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:04,868
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH FRIENDLY?

532
00:42:04,868 --> 00:42:06,868
SOMETIMES, WHEN YOU
LEAST EXPECT IT,

533
00:42:06,868 --> 00:42:09,634
FRIENDSHIP WILL STAB YOU
IN THE BACK LIKE A DAGGER.

534
00:42:09,634 --> 00:42:12,534
THE CUSTOMER WILL START TRUSTING
YOU, YOU'LL START TRUSTING THEM.

535
00:42:12,534 --> 00:42:14,200
ONE THING WILL LEAD
TO ANOTHER

536
00:42:14,200 --> 00:42:15,767
AND YOU DON'T WANT
THAT TO HAPPEN.

537
00:42:15,767 --> 00:42:18,367
CAN I GET ONE
FOR THE ROAD?

538
00:42:18,367 --> 00:42:20,534
NO, SORRY, ROGER.
WE'RE CLOSED.

539
00:42:20,534 --> 00:42:22,133
WAIT, JUST ONE FOR THE ROAD.
COME ON.

540
00:42:22,133 --> 00:42:24,467
I THINK YOU'VE HAD
SEVEN FOR THE ROAD.

541
00:42:24,467 --> 00:42:27,300
- THIS ONE IS FOR THE ROAD.
- WE'RE CLOSED.

542
00:42:29,367 --> 00:42:30,934
DAMN IT.

543
00:42:32,667 --> 00:42:36,801
OH, WHAT IS HAPPENING
TO HUMANITY THESE DAYS?

544
00:42:36,801 --> 00:42:38,834
FUCK.

545
00:42:38,834 --> 00:42:42,300
YOU'RE DOING
ALL RIGHT, LUCAS,

546
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:44,067
BUT YOU STILL GOT
A LOT TO LEARN.

547
00:42:44,067 --> 00:42:45,467
WE GOTTA WORK
ON YOUR ATTITUDE.

548
00:42:45,467 --> 00:42:48,300
I MEAN, YOU'RE NOT
A NATURAL WHEN IT COMES

549
00:42:48,300 --> 00:42:49,868
TO HOSTILITY AND ARROGANCE.

550
00:42:49,868 --> 00:42:53,834
BUT YOU KNOW,
GIVEN TIME IT'LL COME.

551
00:43:09,033 --> 00:43:12,868
IT'S AMAZING

552
00:43:12,868 --> 00:43:17,267
HOW BROCCOLI ALWAYS
MAKES YOU FART.

553
00:43:17,267 --> 00:43:21,067
IN A WAY, BROCCOLI
IS THE EMBODIMENT OF FART.

554
00:43:21,067 --> 00:43:26,167
IF YOU COULD CAPTURE
A PIECE OF FART,

555
00:43:26,167 --> 00:43:28,868
MATERIALIZE IT,

556
00:43:28,868 --> 00:43:32,667
I IMAGINE IT WOULD LOOK
PRETTY MUCH LIKE THIS.

557
00:43:34,934 --> 00:43:37,667
THE INCARNATION OF FART.

558
00:43:48,100 --> 00:43:51,567
LUCAS, MY BOY...

559
00:43:51,567 --> 00:43:55,367
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

560
00:44:29,968 --> 00:44:31,534
HI.

561
00:44:33,734 --> 00:44:35,601
THE BAR IS CLOSED.

562
00:44:42,300 --> 00:44:44,234
OH...

563
00:44:45,767 --> 00:44:47,601
HEY, DON'T CRY.

564
00:44:50,133 --> 00:44:51,767
DON'T CRY.

565
00:44:51,767 --> 00:44:55,400
UH, EVERYTHING IS GOING
TO BE JUST FINE.

566
00:45:03,100 --> 00:45:04,634
HERE, HAVE A SEAT.

567
00:45:11,634 --> 00:45:13,834
LET ME GET YOU
SOMETHING TO DRINK.

568
00:45:13,834 --> 00:45:17,133
- WHAT WOULD YOU LIKE?
- CHAMPAGNE.

569
00:45:18,868 --> 00:45:21,634
- CHAMPAGNE?
- <i>YES, PLEASE.</i>

570
00:45:42,501 --> 00:45:44,767
- HERE.
- THANK YOU.

571
00:45:51,868 --> 00:45:54,601
MM.

572
00:45:59,868 --> 00:46:04,367
- ARE YOU A STEWARDESS?
- NO.

573
00:46:04,367 --> 00:46:06,200
OH.

574
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:11,000
I JUST THOUGHT BECAUSE
OF THE OUTFIT...

575
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:14,767
- I GOT FIRED.
- WHY?

576
00:46:14,767 --> 00:46:17,367
BECAUSE I WAS AFRAID.

577
00:46:17,367 --> 00:46:19,367
AFRAID OF WHAT?

578
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:25,434
I WAS AFRAID OF FLYING.

579
00:46:29,934 --> 00:46:34,267
WELL, IT'S NOT
IN OUR NATURE TO FLY.

580
00:46:34,267 --> 00:46:36,901
SO I DON'T BLAME YOU.

581
00:46:38,901 --> 00:46:40,834
YOU ARE VERY KIND.

582
00:46:49,634 --> 00:46:51,834
CAN I STAY
WITH YOU TONIGHT?

583
00:46:53,367 --> 00:46:54,801
YOU MEAN LIKE--

584
00:46:54,801 --> 00:46:57,534
I HAVE NO PLACE TO SLEEP
AND I'M VERY TIRED.

585
00:46:57,534 --> 00:47:02,334
UM...

586
00:47:02,334 --> 00:47:07,100
I'M AFRAID THAT'S
MAYBE NOT THE BEST IDEA.

587
00:47:07,100 --> 00:47:09,701
OH, NO NO.

588
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:13,901
PLEASE, I AM SORRY.
I AM SORRY.

589
00:47:13,901 --> 00:47:16,434
<i>DON'T CRY.</i>

590
00:47:25,667 --> 00:47:28,234
BUT WE HAVE TO BE
VERY QUIET

591
00:47:28,234 --> 00:47:32,100
AND VERY VERY
CAREFUL.

592
00:47:32,100 --> 00:47:36,033
- WHERE ARE WE GOING?
- I LIVE HERE.

593
00:47:36,033 --> 00:47:37,934
WOW.

594
00:47:37,934 --> 00:47:40,634
MY BOSS
LIVES HERE TOO

595
00:47:40,634 --> 00:47:44,033
AND HE'S NOT
THE KIND OF PERSON

596
00:47:44,033 --> 00:47:46,033
YOU'D LIKE TO WAKE UP
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT.

597
00:47:46,033 --> 00:47:49,033
I UNDERSTAND.

598
00:47:50,834 --> 00:47:52,767
I'M SORRY.

599
00:47:55,267 --> 00:47:57,667
<i>You will be at peace with yourself</i>

600
00:47:57,667 --> 00:48:00,267
<i>and the people</i>
<i>around you.</i>

601
00:48:00,267 --> 00:48:05,534
<i>I am going to wake you up</i>
<i>at the count of five.</i>

602
00:48:07,133 --> 00:48:08,501
<i>One--</i>

603
00:48:08,501 --> 00:48:12,033
<i>you feel yourself</i>
<i>awakening now,</i>

604
00:48:12,033 --> 00:48:16,400
<i>filled with energy</i>
<i>and self-assurance.</i>

605
00:48:16,400 --> 00:48:19,367
<i>Two-- you are</i>
<i>feeling good</i>

606
00:48:19,367 --> 00:48:23,033
<i>and glad to be alive.</i>

607
00:48:23,033 --> 00:48:26,400
<i>Three-- you are</i>
<i>awakening now, feeling...</i>

608
00:48:44,901 --> 00:48:48,901
GOOD MORNING, JACQUES.
THIS IS APRIL.

609
00:48:48,901 --> 00:48:51,067
SHE HAD NO PLACE TO STAY
AND NO MONEY, SO--

610
00:48:51,067 --> 00:48:53,534
I WANT THAT WHORE
OUT OF MY HOUSE IMMEDIATELY

611
00:48:53,534 --> 00:48:55,934
AND I NEVER WANT
TO SEE HER AGAIN.

612
00:49:00,734 --> 00:49:03,834
- DID YOU HEAR WHAT HE
JUST CALLED ME? - YES.

613
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:09,200
CHAMPAGNE IS NOT FOR
WETTING PUSSIES, YOU KNOW.

614
00:49:09,200 --> 00:49:11,667
IT'S FOR CELEBRATING
MAJOR VICTORIES IN SPORTS.

615
00:49:11,667 --> 00:49:15,133
LISTEN TO ME.

616
00:49:15,133 --> 00:49:16,868
THERE ARE TWO WORLDS--

617
00:49:16,868 --> 00:49:18,701
THE WORLD OF MAN
AND THE WORLD OF THE BITCH.

618
00:49:18,701 --> 00:49:20,567
A BAR IS NO PLACE
FOR A WOMAN.

619
00:49:20,567 --> 00:49:22,267
THEY HAVE THE CAFETERIAS
AND THE PATISSERIES.

620
00:49:22,267 --> 00:49:23,968
THE BAR IS OUR SPACE.

621
00:49:23,968 --> 00:49:27,033
IT'S A SANCTUARY WHERE MAN
CAN COME AND BE FREE

622
00:49:27,033 --> 00:49:29,234
KNOWING THAT HE'S
PERFECTLY PROTECTED

623
00:49:29,234 --> 00:49:31,467
FROM ANY INTERFERENCE
OF THE FEMININE.

624
00:49:31,467 --> 00:49:33,968
BUT SHE'S GOT NO MONEY
AND NO PLACE TO STAY.

625
00:49:33,968 --> 00:49:36,534
WELL, THAT'S NOT YOUR PROBLEM
AND IT CERTAINLY ISN'T MINE.

626
00:49:36,534 --> 00:49:40,033
- WE CAN'T JUST THROW HER OUT ON THE
STREET LIKE GARBAGE. - YES, WE CAN.

627
00:49:40,033 --> 00:49:42,434
DON'T YOU HAVE
ANY SYMPATHY FOR PEOPLE?

628
00:49:42,434 --> 00:49:44,234
OH, JESUS CHRIST, LUCAS.
DON'T GIVE ME THAT.

629
00:49:44,234 --> 00:49:46,067
I AM JUST TRYING
TO BE HELPFUL!

630
00:49:46,067 --> 00:49:49,334
WE GOT EVERYTHING.
SHE'S GOT NOTHING.

631
00:49:49,334 --> 00:49:51,534
WE CAN HELP HER.
IT'S THAT SIMPLE.

632
00:49:58,734 --> 00:50:01,100
24 HOURS.

633
00:50:01,100 --> 00:50:04,734
<i>YOU'VE GOT 24 HOURS</i>
<i>TO GET RID OF THE BITCH.</i>

634
00:50:15,834 --> 00:50:19,167
SO HOW ARE YOU
FEELING THESE DAYS?

635
00:50:19,167 --> 00:50:21,601
DOUBT, FEAR,

636
00:50:21,601 --> 00:50:24,968
PAIN, ANXIETY,

637
00:50:24,968 --> 00:50:27,834
DISTRACTION,
NERVOUSNESS,

638
00:50:27,834 --> 00:50:31,033
HORROR, FRIGHT,
PANIC, DREAD,

639
00:50:31,033 --> 00:50:34,267
TERROR, TREPIDATION.

640
00:50:34,267 --> 00:50:36,667
I FEEL LIKE
A GODDAMN THESAURUS.

641
00:50:36,667 --> 00:50:39,667
COME ON, ESTRAGON,
EAT THOSE HERBS.

642
00:50:39,667 --> 00:50:41,367
THEY'RE GOOD FOR YOU.

643
00:50:41,367 --> 00:50:43,634
LOOKS GOOD.

644
00:50:56,734 --> 00:50:58,367
WHERE IS YOUR LADY ROOM?

645
00:50:58,367 --> 00:51:00,634
NO LADY ROOM.

646
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:07,934
ESTRAGON?

647
00:51:11,501 --> 00:51:13,367
